{{Quote|You are summoned, Wat Tambor of the Crimlin clan. Come now, to the Power Mounds of the Elders!|An Elder, to Wat Tambor|<ref name="Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops">{{StoryCite|story=Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops|book=Star Wars: Visionaries}}</ref>}}
The '''Power Mounds of the Elders''',<ref name="Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops" /> also known simply as the '''Power Mounds''',<ref name="Planet Hoppers">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/PHSkako|series=Planet Hoppers|text=Skako}}</ref> were an exclusive site<ref name="Power Mounds of the Elders" /> located in the [[Clouds of Cormelish]]<ref name="Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops" /> on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Skako/Legends|Skako]] where the [[Elders (Skakoan)|Elders]], the ruling body of the [[Skakoan/Legends|Skakoans]], would gather.<ref name="Power Mounds of the Elders" /> The Skakoan [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld's]] most sacred site, it factored heavily into their complex [[Skakoan religion|religion]] and was the resting place of the [[Book of the Boolmide]], which was kept and read by the Elders.<ref name="Planet Hoppers" /> Few were invited to the mounds;<ref name="Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops" /> chosen individuals who traveled there and read from the book could open the [[Gates of Grontessiant]], a supposedly mythical realm.<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />

After losing an [[Eye/Legends|eye]] to [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Wat Tambor/Legends|Wat Tambor]] of the [[Crimlin clan]] was summoned to the Power Mounds by the Elders.<ref name="Wat Tambor and the Quest for the Sacred Eye of the Albino Cyclops" />

